#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:252
msgid "Booting from a floppy using syslinux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:254
msgid ""
"When building kernels, an easy way to create a boot floppy that uses "
"syslinux is to use the zdisk or bzdisk make targets which use zimage and "
"bzimage images respectively. Both targets accept the FDARGS parameter which "
"can be used to set the kernel command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:259
#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:282
#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:290
#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:306
msgid "e.g::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:263
msgid ""
"Note that the user running this command will need to have access to the "
"floppy drive device, /dev/fd0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:266
msgid ""
"For more information on syslinux, including how to create bootdisks for "
"prebuilt kernels, see https://syslinux.zytor.com/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:270
msgid ""
"Previously it was possible to write a kernel directly to a floppy using dd, "
"configure the boot device using rdev, and boot using the resulting floppy. "
"Linux no longer supports this method of booting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:275
msgid "Booting from a cdrom using isolinux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:277
msgid ""
"When building kernels, an easy way to create a bootable cdrom that uses "
"isolinux is to use the isoimage target which uses a bzimage image. Like "
"zdisk and bzdisk, this target accepts the FDARGS parameter which can be used "
"to set the kernel command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:286
msgid ""
"The resulting iso image will be arch/<ARCH>/boot/image.iso This can be "
"written to a cdrom using a variety of tools including cdrecord."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:294
#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:348
msgid ""
"For more information on isolinux, including how to create bootdisks for "
"prebuilt kernels, see https://syslinux.zytor.com/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:297
msgid "Using LILO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:299
msgid ""
"When using LILO all the necessary command line parameters may be specified "
"using the 'append=' directive in the LILO configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:303
msgid ""
"However, to use the 'root=' directive you also need to create a dummy root "
"device, which may be removed after LILO is run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:310
msgid "For information on configuring LILO, please refer to its documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:312
msgid "Using GRUB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:314
msgid ""
"When using GRUB, kernel parameter are simply appended after the kernel "
"specification: kernel <kernel> <parameters>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:317
msgid "Using loadlin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:319
msgid ""
"loadlin may be used to boot Linux from a DOS command prompt without "
"requiring a local hard disk to mount as root. This has not been thoroughly "
"tested by the authors of this document, but in general it should be possible "
"configure the kernel command line similarly to the configuration of LILO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:325
msgid "Please refer to the loadlin documentation for further information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:327
msgid "Using a boot ROM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:329
msgid ""
"This is probably the most elegant way of booting a diskless client. With a "
"boot ROM the kernel is loaded using the TFTP protocol. The authors of this "
"document are not aware of any no commercial boot ROMs that support booting "
"Linux over the network. However, there are two free implementations of a "
"boot ROM, netboot-nfs and etherboot, both of which are available on sunsite."
"unc.edu, and both of which contain everything you need to boot a diskless "
"Linux client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:337
msgid "Using pxelinux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:339
msgid ""
"Pxelinux may be used to boot linux using the PXE boot loader which is "
"present on many modern network cards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsroot.rst:342
msgid ""
"When using pxelinux, the kernel image is specified using \"kernel <relative-"
"path-below /tftpboot>\". The nfsroot parameters are passed to the kernel by "
"adding them to the \"append\" line. It is common to use serial console in "
"conjunction with pxeliunx, see Documentation/admin-guide/serial-console.rst "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

